> *Second: *TCS threshold hard-coded in SP must be added as a Critical 
> Defect. Seenivasan confirmed in the IST review that the TCS threshold 
> is handled within KSP_TCSAmountCheckLSales SP logic and is not 
> separately configurable in any table. The CEO directed this to be 
> added to Section 12 as a Critical Defect. It is not there. Please add 
> it: CD-7 — TCS threshold hard-coded in KSP_TCSAmountCheckLSales SP. 
> Not configurable. *SPINRISE fix: move threshold to a dedicated TCS 
> configuration table read as a parameter by the SP.*
>
> *Third:* Section 5.6 Document Number Generation needs a warning 
> callout. CD-1 correctly identifies the race condition in Section 12. 
> But Section 5.6 describes the IG_DOCCONTROL generation mechanism 
> without flagging that the current implementation lacks UPDLOCK. *Add a 
> single warning line: 'CRITICAL DEFECT CD-1: This MAX+1 read is 
> performed WITHOUT UPDLOCK. See Section 12.1 for fix.'
> *
> *On Section 13 IST answers — what I am seeing
> *
> *Annamalai, I need to be direct about something important. *Seven of 
> the thirteen IST questions in Section 13 have answers that read as 
> 'Default values N' or 'Default values 0' or 'Default values 100'. 
> These are not IST answers. These are the default values from Section 
> 11 that you have already correctly documented. IST-1 asks which live 
> customers have non-standard ig_param settings — that answer is not 
> 'Default values N.' IST-2 asks who sets App_Flg after a sale order is 
> saved — that answer is not 'Default values N.' IST-4 asks which live 
> customers have CRLimitLockFlg='Y' — Seenivasan already told us in the 
> IST mail exchange that only Bannari uses it. Why is that not recorded 
> here?
>
> *Section 13 can only be completed by Seenivasan from his field 
> experience at customer sites.* You cannot complete it from the code. 
> The defaults belong in Section 11 — which you have correctly done. The 
> IST answers belong in Section 13 — which only Seenivasan can provide.
>
> I understand you may have added these default values to make the 
> document appear complete before submission. *Do not do this. *An FSD 
> with fabricated IST answers is worse than one with blank IST fields, 
> because it obscures what is actually missing. *Leave the IST fields 
> blank or mark them '[Seenivasan — IST answer required]' and submit to 
> Seenivasan immediately.
> *
> *For Seenivasan — IST-1 to IST-13 answers due Monday 13 April AN.*
>
> Seenivasan, the v3 FSD is technically ready for IST review. The 
> developer has done his part and done it well. Your IST review of 
> Section 13 is the gating step. You need to answer all 13 IST questions 
> from your own field experience. Several of these you have already 
> answered in the mail exchange — do not repeat the work, simply 
> transfer those answers into Section 13 directly.
>
> IST-4: You already confirmed only Bannari uses CRLimitLockFlg='Y'. 
> Record this.
> IST-7: You already confirmed IG_PARAM.Despatch_Instruction controls 
> the IG_INSBODT vs IG_BODT routing. Record this.
> IST-9: You confirmed CSM is not live — but a customer used it and 
> plans to reuse. Record which customer.
> IST-10: You confirmed automail is not used by any customer currently. 
> Record this.
> IST-8: You confirmed TCS threshold is hard-coded in the SP. Record this.
>
> For the questions where you have not yet provided answers in the mail 
> thread — IST-1 (non-standard ig_param settings at live sites), IST-2 
> (App_Flg approval screen name and user role), IST-3 (pending order 
> value includes only approved orders — is this correct?), IST-5 
> (minimum 5 support call patterns), IST-6 (JW only or other contract 
> types), IST-11 (RepLSales.rpt — multiple versions across sites?), 
> IST-12 (what is handled manually at year-end?) —*these are the fresh 
> answers needed.*
>
> *Also: the two follow-ups from the earlier CEO mail that remain open.* 
> CRLimitLockFlg='N' path — when the Yes/No warning appears, can any 
> logged-in user override or is there a user-level check? And the Scrap 
> Sales contract type code — what is the exact code in ig_conttype that 
> represents Scrap Sales, since TCS applies only to that contract type?
>
> *Deadline for Seenivasan:* complete and send your Section 13 IST 
> answers to Annamalai by *Monday 13 April, 4:00 PM.*
>
> *For TL-IST Palanivel — TL-IST sign-off deadline Monday 13 April 6.00PM.
> *
> Once Seenivasan sends his IST answers and Annamalai incorporates them, 
> the document goes to you for TL-IST independent review. Your review 
> must follow the checklist standard — agree or correct each IST answer 
> from your own senior IST experience, do not simply forward. Given the 
