>>>
>>> *This is a substantial revision and the effort is visible.* Between 
>>> 2 April and today, ten sections that were either absent or 
>>> inadequate have been brought to a proper standard. Let me be specific.
>>>
>>> Section 3 (Field Rules) is new and covers 25 fields with mandatory 
>>> flags, data types, lengths, defaults, and notes. Section 4 
>>> (Validation Rules) is now correctly structured into four categories 
>>> — Pre-Add, Header, Line Entry, and Customer-Specific — with error 
>>> messages inline. This was entirely absent in version 1. Section 6 
>>> (TC Framework) is now present and correctly states that the Sale 
>>> Order form does not trigger stock movements or accounting entries at 
>>> the point of order creation — TC activation happens downstream at 
>>> despatch and invoice. This is the correct understanding and it 
>>> protects the SPINRISE developer from building the wrong integration 
>>> point.
>>>
>>> Section 7 (Common Module Dependencies) now analyses Spinmod.bas, 
>>> modGeneral.bas, and clsCrystal.cls at the function level. Section 8 
>>> (DB Operations) now documents both KSP_LSALES_SALEORDER and 
>>> KSP_TCSAmountCheckLSales with their business rules. Section 9 (Error 
>>> Messages) is entirely new — 39 exact messages with trigger 
>>> conditions. Sections 12 (SPINRISE Recommendations), 13 (IST Review 
>>> Questions), and 14 (Summary Scorecard) are all new additions. This 
>>> is a complete restructuring of the document and it is aligned with 
>>> the v2 template.
>>>
>>> *This is the level of quality that should have been in the first 
>>> submission.* That said, the first submission was made on 2 April — 
>>> eight days before the current date — and Seenivasan had eight days 
>>> to review it and provide feedback. No IST feedback was provided. I 
>>> will address that separately below.
